Msunduzi Municipality has reported several Medium Voltage (MV) trips from different parts of the City on Tuesday morning. Apart from MV trips, stage two loadshedding has also been implemented until further notice by Eskom. The MV trips were at Pine Primary to Taunton Fettes,Â  Hesketh Primary to Gladys Manzi Grimthorpe, Prince Alfred Primary to Christie Ritchie, Prince Alfred Primary to Prince Alfred No.1, Riverside Primary to Royston Tucker, Mayor's walk Exchange No. 1, Mkondeni Primary to Chad Oribi and Mysore Lahore. A suspected MV trip at Balhambra Lupin affecting Mount view, Woodpecker, Claridge and surrounding areas was also reported. Other areas affected by the MV trips: Wembley, parts old howick, Athlone, parts of Montrose, and surrounding areas * Lincoln Meade, Darvill, parts of Bishopstowe and surrounding areas * Pelham, part of Scottsville, Southgate, Southland, Richmond Crest, Parts of Bisley, and surrounding areas * Camps drift, Napierville and surrounding areas * Mountain rise and surrounding areas * Prestbury, Boughton, Mpumuza, Uplands, Parts of Blackridge, Morcom road and surrounding areas * Mkondeni, Part of Oribi and surrounding areas * Bombay, Karupana, ramatha, nulliah and surrounding areas The City also reported that supply was restored from a trip at Hesketh Primary to Gladys Manzi Grimthorpe and only part of Grimthop and part of Bishopstowe. A crossing Msunduzi River was off by 6 am for further faults locating. Fault between Prince Alfred Primary and Christie Ritchie required further fault locating. The City added due to adverse weather conditions and influx of outage complaints, delays can be expected in the restoration of power. They said single complaints are attended as and when logged via the call center or faults office.